3. Section 151.09 is amended by adding paragraphs (c) and (d) to read as follows:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;151.09
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Applicability.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=37 g=1 f=1 -->
* * * * *
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(c) Sections 151.26 through 151.28 apply to each United States oceangoing ship specified in paragraphs (a)(1) through
(a)(4) of this section which is_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) An oil tanker of 150 gross tons and above or other ship of 400 gross tons and above; or
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) A fixed or floating drilling rig or other platform, when not engaged in the exploration, exploitation, or associated
offshore processing of seabed mineral resources.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) Sections 151.26 through 151.28 do not apply to_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The ships specified in paragraph (b) of this section;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Any barge or other ship which is constructed or operated in such a manner that no oil can be discharged from any portion
thereof, intentionally or unintentionally, including, but not limited to, oil discharged as the result of a casualty
to the ship.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

